The paper discusses a visual analytics approach to understanding the dynamics of deep RNNs in sequence classification tasks. This involves revealing the RNN attention for all data instances, their temporal positions in the sequences, and the attribution of variables at each value level. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with deep learning models and their interpretability, which are central topics in these fields. The other categories are also relevant, as the paper discusses sequence classification and feature attribution, which are important in computer vision, natural language processing, and information retrieval.
